Biography

At Utah Valley ...

Sophomore (2022-23): Played in 22 games ... named to College Sports Communicators Academic All-District Team ... named to Academic All-WAC Team ... averaged 1.2 points and 1.0 rebound per game ... scored season-high seven points at Abilene Christian.

Freshman (2021-22): Appeared in 11 games ... registered first career double-double with 10 points and 12 rebounds (both season highs) in win over New Mexico State.

Before Utah Valley ...

Prepped at Lone Peak High School in Highland, Utah ... four-year letter-winner ... two-time 6A All-State selection including third team as a senior after averaging 10 points and six rebounds per game ... was also a three-time All-Region and All-Valley selection ... helped team to a #2 ranking and a region championship as a senior ... also was part of a state semifinals team and two quarterfinals teams during prep career ... high school coach was Nancy Warner ... played club for Natalie Williams Basketball Academy, Hoops ASL, Utah Flash and the Helena Fever.

Personal ...

Parents are Alanna and John ... born in Helena, Montana ... has three sisters (Camryn, Kadyn, Ella) and one brother (John Christian) ... dad played baseball at UVU (then UVSC) in 1995 ... enjoys playing the piano ... favorite teams are the Utah Jazz and New York Liberty and favorite athletes are Sabrina Ionescu and Mike Conley ... has done volunteer work feeding and making care packages for the homeless.

No stats available for the current season.
